            "It appears that the TLC has implemented rules to increase the minimum per-mile rate to account for increased driver expenses, but the specific details of these changes are not provided in the given context. To determine the exact details of the TLC's rules regarding driver pay, further information or a more comprehensive source would be necessary.\n",
            "\n",
            "Additionally, the context mentions that the TLC adopted rules to implement Local Laws 33 and 56 of 2024, which authorize interior advertising in for-hire vehicles and require related advertising revenue compensation for drivers. However, this information does not directly address driver pay, but rather a separate aspect of TLC regulations.\n",
