      "source": [
        "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer, util\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "#Step 1: Create test set\n",
        "test_set = [\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"What policies regulate taxi fares in NYC?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"TLC sets fare rates through official rules published in the TLC regulations.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"How does Vision Zero impact taxi operations?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"Vision Zero policies require stricter safety compliance and reporting for taxis.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"What trends are reported in TLC annual ridership?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"Taxi ridership has slowed since 2013, with ride-hailing apps increasing the for-hire vehicle supply.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"What are the rules on surge pricing?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"TLC regulates surge pricing through fare caps and official rate adjustments.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"How are driver tips and fare structures documented?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"TLC requires reporting of driver tips and maintains standard fare structures in its regulations.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"What licensing requirements apply to taxi drivers?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"Taxi drivers must be licensed by the TLC, meeting training, background check, and compliance requirements.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"What insurance policies are mandated for for-hire vehicles?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"TLC requires for-hire vehicles to carry minimum liability and personal injury insurance coverage.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"What accessibility requirements exist for NYC taxis?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"TLC mandates that a percentage of taxis be wheelchair accessible, with compliance targets set in regulations.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"What safety measures are outlined in DOT publications?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"DOT publications emphasize reduced speed limits, Vision Zero initiatives, and stricter enforcement to improve safety.\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"question\": \"How do TLC rules address driver pay?\",\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": \"TLC regulations establish minimum pay standards for drivers of for-hire vehicles to ensure fair compensation.\"\n",
        "    }\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "sim_model = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n",
        "threshold = 0.65\n",
        "\n",
        "correct_count = 0\n",
        "results = []\n",
        "\n",
        "for item in test_set:\n",
        "    q = item[\"question\"]\n",
        "    gold = item[\"gold_answer\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "    result = qa_chain.invoke({\"query\": q})\n",
        "    answer = result[\"result\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Split into sentences and find the most similar one to the gold answer\n",
        "    sentences = [s.strip() for s in answer.replace(\"\\n\", \" \").split(\".\") if len(s.strip()) > 20]\n",
        "\n",
        "    emb_gold = sim_model.encode(gold, convert_to_tensor=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if sentences:\n",
        "        emb_sentences = sim_model.encode(sentences, convert_to_tensor=True)\n",
        "        sims = util.cos_sim(emb_gold, emb_sentences)[0] # use cosin to measure how close the sentences are\n",
        "        similarity = sims.max().item()  # best matching sentence\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        emb_answer = sim_model.encode(answer, convert_to_tensor=True)\n",
        "        similarity = util.cos_sim(emb_gold, emb_answer).item()\n",
        "\n",
        "    answer_ok = similarity >= threshold\n",
        "    if answer_ok:\n",
        "        correct_count += 1\n",
        "\n",
        "    results.append({\n",
        "        \"question\": q,\n",
        "        \"gold_answer\": gold,\n",
        "        \"generated_answer\": answer,\n",
        "        \"similarity\": round(similarity, 2),\n",
        "        \"answer_ok\": answer_ok\n",
        "    })\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nQ: {q}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Gold: {gold}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Generated: {answer}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Semantic similarity: {similarity:.2f}\")\n",
        "    print(\"-\" * 50)\n",
        "\n",
        "accuracy = correct_count / len(test_set) * 100\n",
        "print(f\"\\nPipeline semantic accuracy: {accuracy:.1f}%\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The similarity threshold was set at 0.65 because lower thresholds (like 0.6) were too permissive giving a 100% accuracy, by accepting weak matches, while higher thresholds (like 0.7) were overly strict, discarding answers that were partially correct and giving a 0.0%. At 0.65, the pipeline achieved 50% semantic accuracy, which provides a balanced reflection of answer quality neither inflated nor overly harsh.\n",
