        "Q3: TLC ridership trends\n",
        "  Failure: Retrieval — captured TNC growth but missed slowdown trend since 2013.  \n",
        "  Improvement: Use smaller chunk sizes or increase top‑k retrieval to surface slowdown passages.\n",
        "\n",
        "Q4: Surge pricing rules  \n",
        "  Failure: Retrieval — retrieved policy suggestions but not TLC’s official fare caps.  \n",
        "  Improvement: Improve retriever filtering to prioritize TLC regulatory documents over proposals.\n",
        "\n",
        "Q5: Tips and fare structures  \n",
        "  Failure: Generation — speculated about fare levels without confirming tip documentation.  \n",
        "  Improvement: Strengthen prompt to discourage speculation and require explicit references.\n",
        "\n",
        "Q6: Licensing requirements\n",
        "The generated answer aligned well with the gold, correctly mentioning TLC licensing, training, and compliance but it didn’t emphasize background checks as strongly. However itmentioned another Chicago which drift from the context\n",
        "Improvement: Ensure retriever surfaces passages that explicitly list all licensing requirements, not just general compliance.\n",
        "\n",
        "Q7: Insurance policies\n",
        "Failure: The generated answer was vague, referencing “insurance coverage” but not specifying liability and personal injury minimums.\n",
        "Improvement: Refine retrieval to prioritize TLC regulatory text that explicitly states mandated coverage levels. Prompt should require citing exact policy types.\n",
        "\n",
        "Q8: Accessibility requirements\n",
        "The answer captured wheelchair accessibility mandates and compliance targets, closely matching the gold. It lacked detail on the percentage requirement.\n",
        "Improvement: Increase top‑k retrieval or use smaller chunks to surface numeric compliance targets.\n",
        "\n",
        "Q9: DOT safety measures\n",
        "Failure: The generated answer mentioned safety broadly but missed reduced speed limits and enforcement emphasis.\n",
        "Improvement: Tune retriever to prioritize DOT publications with explicit Vision Zero references and numeric safety measures.\n",
        "\n",
        "Q10: Driver pay rules\n",
        "The generated answer aligned well, correctly noting minimum pay standards for for‑hire drivers but it didn’t emphasize “fair compensation” language.\n",
        "Improvement: Adjust prompt to encourage inclusion of regulatory phrasing, not just paraphrased summarie\n",
        "\n",
        "Semantic similarity was used because it measures whether generated answers convey the same meaning as the gold reference, even if phrased differently. A keyword‑based evaluation gave only 30% accuracy, penalizing answers that were phrased differently but still correct. Semantic similarity is better suited for policy and regulatory language, where nuance matters more than exact word overlap, making it a more faithful measure of pipeline quality.\n"
