      "source": [
        "from langchain_core.prompts import PromptTemplate\n",
        "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n",
        "from langchain.chains import LLMChain\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "llm = ChatOpenAI(\n",
        "    temperature=0,\n",
        "    openai_api_base=\"https://synapse.sergiomathurin.com/v1\",\n",
        "    openai_api_key=os.getenv(\"LLM_API_KEY\"),\n",
        "    model=\"llama3-8b-instruct\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 1: SQL generation prompt\n",
        "sql_prompt = \"\"\"\n",
        "You are an assistant that converts natural language questions into Spark SQL queries.\n",
        "\n",
        "The SQL must query the 'trips' view.\n",
        "\n",
        "IMPORTANT:\n",
        "- Use ONLY the following columns:\n",
        "  fare_amount, trip_distance, tip_amount, total_amount,\n",
        "  pickup_hour, pickup_day_of_week, trip_speed_mph, trip_duration_minutes, tip_percentage\n",
        "\n",
        "- pickup_day_of_week is a STRING (e.g., 'Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', etc.)\n",
        "- Do NOT use columns that do not exist (e.g., fare, dayofweek)\n",
        "- ALWAYS aggregate results using AVG, COUNT, SUM, MIN, MAX, or GROUP BY\n",
        "- NEVER return raw rows — always summarize\n",
        "\n",
        "Only output the SQL query. No explanations. No markdown.\n",
        "\n",
        "Question: {question}\n",
        "SQL:\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "sql_template = PromptTemplate(input_variables=[\"question\"], template=sql_prompt)\n",
        "sql_chain = LLMChain(llm=llm, prompt=sql_template)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 2: Answer synthesis prompt\n",
        "answer_prompt = \"\"\"\n",
        "You are an assistant that explains SQL query results in natural language.\n",
        "Given the question, SQL query, and raw results, synthesize a concise answer.\n",
        "\n",
        "Question: {question}\n",
        "SQL: {sql}\n",
        "Results: {results}\n",
        "Answer:\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "answer_template = PromptTemplate(input_variables=[\"question\", \"sql\", \"results\"], template=answer_prompt)\n",
        "answer_chain = LLMChain(llm=llm, prompt=answer_template)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 3: Handler function (no prints inside)\n",
        "def handle_data_query(question):\n",
        "    sql_output = sql_chain.invoke({\"question\": question})\n",
        "    sql = sql_output[\"text\"].strip()\n",
        "\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        results = spark.sql(f\"SELECT * FROM ({sql}) AS subq LIMIT 20\").collect()\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        retry_prompt = f\"\"\"\n",
        "You are fixing a Spark SQL query.\n",
        "\n",
        "Original question: {question}\n",
        "Previous SQL: {sql}\n",
        "Error: {str(e)}\n",
        "\n",
        "Return ONLY the corrected SQL query. No markdown. Must aggregate results.\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "        retry_chain = LLMChain(\n",
        "            llm=llm,\n",
        "            prompt=PromptTemplate(input_variables=[], template=retry_prompt)\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        sql = retry_chain.invoke({})[\"text\"].strip()\n",
        "        results = spark.sql(f\"SELECT * FROM ({sql}) AS subq LIMIT 20\").collect()\n",
        "\n",
        "    answer_output = answer_chain.invoke({\n",
        "        \"question\": question,\n",
        "        \"sql\": sql,\n",
        "        \"results\": str(results)\n",
        "    })\n",
        "\n",
        "    return sql, results, answer_output[\"text\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 4: Test\n",
        "test_questions = [\n",
        "    \"What was the average fare on Mondays?\",\n",
        "    \"Which pickup hour has the highest trip count?\",\n",
        "    \"What is the average trip speed on weekends?\",\n",
        "    \"How many trips exceeded $100 in fare?\",\n",
        "    \"What is the median tip percentage for short trips?\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "#print answer here to avoid double printing\n",
        "for q in test_questions:\n",
        "    print(\"\\n---\")\n",
        "    print(\"Question:\", q)\n",
        "    sql, results, answer = handle_data_query(q)\n",
        "    print(\"Generated SQL:\", sql)\n",
        "    print(\"Raw Results:\", results)\n",
        "    print(\"Final Answer:\", answer)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "This cell sets up a two‑stage handler for DATA queries by first using an LLM prompt to translate natural language questions into valid Spark SQL statements against the trips view, then executing those queries to produce structured results. Once the raw output is collected, a second prompt synthesizes the findings into concise natural language answers that are easy to interpret. The design also includes built‑in error correction if the initial SQL fails, where the handler automatically retries with a corrected query. This workflow demonstrates how the system bridges natural language input with structured data analysis, producing clear answers such as average fares, trip counts, or median tip percentages while maintaining resilience against query errors."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "OFZ_kXOa25SS"
      }
    },
