      "source": [
        "import json\n",
        "\n",
        "demo_queries = [\n",
        "    # DATA\n",
        "    \"What was the average fare on Mondays?\",\n",
        "    \"Which pickup hour has the highest trip count?\",\n",
        "\n",
        "    # DOCUMENT\n",
        "    \"What are the TLC regulations on surge pricing?\",\n",
        "    \"How does Vision Zero affect taxi operations?\",\n",
        "\n",
        "    # HYBRID\n",
        "    \"How do actual tipping patterns compare to TLC recommendations?\",\n",
        "    \"Do fare trends align with DOT policy goals?\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "for q in demo_queries:\n",
        "    print(\"\\n==============================\")\n",
        "    print(\"User Query:\", q)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Step 1: Classification\n",
        "    classification_output = router_chain.invoke({\"question\": q})[\"text\"]\n",
        "    print(\"Classification Output:\", classification_output)\n",
        "\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        classification_json = json.loads(classification_output)\n",
        "        classification = classification_json.get(\"category\", \"\").upper()\n",
        "    except json.JSONDecodeError:\n",
        "        classification = classification_output.strip().upper()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Step 2: Routing decision\n",
        "    if classification == \"DATA\":\n",
        "        print(\"Routing to Spark SQL handler...\")\n",
        "        sql, results, answer = handle_data_query(q)\n",
        "        print(\"Generated SQL:\", sql)\n",
        "        print(\"Raw Results:\", results)\n",
        "        print(\"Final Answer:\", answer)\n",
        "\n",
        "    elif classification == \"DOCUMENT\":\n",
        "        print(\"Routing to RAG pipeline...\")\n",
        "        result = qa_chain.invoke(q)\n",
        "        retrieved = retriever.get_relevant_documents(q)\n",
        "        print(\"Final Answer:\", result[\"result\"])\n",
        "        print(\"\\n--- Document Sources ---\")\n",
        "        for doc in retrieved[:2]:\n",
        "            print(f\"Source: {doc.metadata.get('source')} Page: {doc.metadata.get('page')}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    elif classification == \"HYBRID\":\n",
        "        print(\"Routing to both Spark SQL and RAG...\")\n",
        "        sql, results, data_answer = handle_data_query(q)\n",
        "        doc_result = qa_chain.invoke(q)\n",
        "        doc_answer = doc_result[\"result\"]\n",
        "        retrieved = retriever.get_relevant_documents(q)\n",
        "        print(\"Generated SQL:\", sql)\n",
        "        print(\"Raw Results:\", results)\n",
        "        print(\"\\n--- Document Sources ---\")\n",
        "        for doc in retrieved[:2]:\n",
        "            print(f\"Source: {doc.metadata.get('source')} Page: {doc.metadata.get('page')}\")\n",
        "        combined_answer = f\"Data insights: {data_answer}\\nDocument insights: {doc_answer}\"\n",
        "        print(\"\\nFinal Combined Answer:\", combined_answer)\n",
        "\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(\"Unable to classify query. Please check router_chain output.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "What types of questions does it handle well?\n",
        "The system handles DATA queries very well anything that can be answered directly from the structured taxi trip dataset (e.g., average fares, busiest pickup hours, tipping percentages). These are routed to Spark SQL, which produces precise, factually correct numeric results. It also does reasonably well with HYBRID queries on the data side, where SQL can provide strong quantitative insights.\n",
        "\n",
        "Where does it fail?\n",
        "The pipeline struggles with DOCUMENT queries and the document side of HYBRID queries. Retrieval sometimes pulls tangential or incomplete chunks, and generation occasionally hallucinates or speculates when the source material doesn’t explicitly cover the question (e.g. Vision Zero’s impact, surge pricing rules). This leads to partial or inaccurate answers. Failures are often due to missing coverage of the corpus or the model drifting away from the retrieved text.\n",
        "\n",
        "How would you improve it with more time?\n",
        "With more time, the improvements I would focus on are adding more authoritative TLC and DOT policy documents to ensure coverage of regulatory questions, retriever tuning, experimenting with chunk sizes, metadata filtering to reduce irrelevant context and prompt refinement to stick closely to retrieved text and avoiding speculation."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RWwPRDZqgjz1"
      }
